Myasthenia gravis (MG) is a chronic autoimmune disease caused by autoantigen 
against the nicotine acetylcholine receptor at the neuromuscular junction. With 
modern treatment facilities, the treatment effect and outcome for MG has been 
greatly improved with MG and non-MG patients enjoying the same life expectancy. 
